overview: The user initiated a request for thorough browser-based testing of the
  sleep questionnaire application. The assistant systematically tested the
  application's key features, starting with the main questionnaire flow,
  including navigation, form validation, and conditional field rendering. It
  utilized a "Pre-fill & Jump to Report (Dev)" button to efficiently test the
  report generation and PDF download functionality. Subsequently, the admin
  dashboard's login protection and error handling were verified. API endpoints
  for responses and PDF generation were also tested, confirming correct
  validation and functionality. While most features performed as expected, the
  assistant identified minor issues such as ESLint warnings and an outdated page
  title, providing recommendations for improvement. The overall outcome
  confirmed the application's robust functionality and identified areas for
  minor refinement.
